26
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,810
To be honest,

27
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:24,620
Wang Yishao and I are pure enemies.

28
00:03:25,070 --> 00:03:26,829
But we are also friends.

29
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,730
How can enemies be friends?

30
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,070
We are enemies

31
00:03:32,070 --> 00:03:34,120
due to some special reasons.

32
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:35,940
But from a human perspective,

33
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,760
some people are born to get along well.

34
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:39,770
In other words, they're the same type.

35
00:03:40,750 --> 00:03:42,520
That makes them natural friends.

36
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,510
Natural friends?

37
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:46,380
Is there such a statement?

38
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,310
Of course.

39
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:48,650
Think about it.

40
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:51,670
Why can't sheep and wolves become friends?

41
00:03:51,810 --> 00:03:53,910
Because wolves eat sheep.

42
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:56,240
