186
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,260
The examples of cows and sheep you took

187
00:13:42,290 --> 00:13:44,680
seem a bit unreasonable.

188
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,200
Sometimes, examples used to make a point

189
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:49,760
don't stand up to close examination.

190
00:13:49,780 --> 00:13:52,040
As long as the point is made, that's enough.

191
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:54,730
Taking examples is just an approach.

192
00:13:54,820 --> 00:13:57,280
If every point can be justified by examples,

193
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:59,590
the more you think about it, the more it seems wrong.

194
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:01,830
That makes sense.

195
00:14:02,090 --> 00:14:03,260
No wonder

196
00:14:03,390 --> 00:14:05,550
the more I thought about it, the stranger it felt.

197
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:07,350
Yeah, I don't understand either.

198
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:09,300
How can cows and sheep become friends?

199
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:10,910
They can't speak.

200
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,530
They can't go out to have fun together either.

201
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:15,070
It can be counted as an appointment

202
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:17,450
when they eat grass together.

203
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:20,670
I saw cows and sheep together.

204
00:14:20,690 --> 00:14:22,280
They seemed very close.

205
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:25,570
I also saw pigs and sheep rubbing against each other.

206
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:28,060
I saw a goose standing on a cow.

207
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:29,180
Yes.

208
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:31,390
I even saw a chicken standing on a cow.

209
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:32,850
I saw something even weirder.

210
00:14:33,060 --> 00:14:36,040
A little bird was pecking on the back of a cow.

211
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:38,050
But the cow was not angry.

212
00:14:39,130 --> 00:14:41,130
Qing Cai is really something.

213
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,210
He managed to talk them

214
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:46,030
into letting Gan Pu out.

215
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:50,100
He even managed to make those who had a grudge against Gan Pu

216
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,080
let go of their hostility.

217
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,510
He's such a talented man.

218
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:54,180
What a pity.

219
00:15:39,010 --> 00:15:41,430
How come your makeup looks different from others'?

220
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,770
Why?

221
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,000
It seems...

222
00:15:46,810 --> 00:15:47,820
